# Senior analysis

When the user asks for a **senior analysis**, **analyze approach**, **design alternatives**, **logical change analysis**, or a **before/after review**, follow **`CANONICAL_DOCS_PATH/senior-analysis.md`**.

When the user asks for **code review**, **review branch**, or **prepare for PR**, follow **`CANONICAL_DOCS_PATH/code-review.md`** instead.

Decompose into logical units (`LC-1`, `LC-2`, …). State tier (Deep / Light / Skip). Unit verdicts: **Sound** | **Acceptable with follow-ups** | **Rethink** — not Ready/Blocked.

When the user asks to **save senior analysis locally**, write to **`.senior-analyses/YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM-<branch-slug>.md`** only (gitignored).

Do not post full reports to PR/ticket systems unless the user explicitly wants a short executive summary.

Recommend code review as follow-up when application source changed.

Replace `CANONICAL_DOCS_PATH` with your repo path. The bundle default layout is `docs/workflows/`.
